The paper discusses the training of structured prediction energy networks (SPENs) using a reward function, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are common areas for structured prediction tasks. Finally, the paper discusses the use of SPENs for security applications (cs.CR), which is a less likely but still plausible sub-category.
